 makers, academics, researchers and students of social policy, social geography, sociology and politics. Members of NGOs working with refugees or in local government, community workers and members of refugee communities themselves will also be keenly interested in the book. Comparative issues raised by the research will be of direct interest to readers in other countries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aCommunity organizationzGreat Britain. 0aNon-governmental organizations. 0aRefugeeszGreat Britain. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aSigona, Nando, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aZetter, Roger, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978186134633940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847421395423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847421395/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles